# Unit Tests Directory

This directory contains unit tests that can be run inside the service container.

Unit tests should:
- Test individual components in isolation
- Use mocks/stubs for dependencies
- Be fast and independent
- Not require external services (MongoDB, Kafka)

## Running Unit Tests

```bash
# Inside container
npm test

# With coverage
npm run test:coverage

# Watch mode
npm run test:watch
```

## Example Test Structure

```
test/unit/
├── application/
│   └── services/
│       └── UserService.test.ts
├── domain/
│   └── entities/
│       └── User.test.ts
└── infrastructure/
    ├── database/
    │   └── MongoUserRepository.test.ts
    └── messaging/
        └── KafkaEventPublisher.test.ts
